PressureProcess
===============

PressureProcess is a Python pipeline for wall-pressure and freestream-pressure
processing. It reads raw MATLAB files, computes calibration transfer functions,
writes intermediate and processed HDF5 products, and can generate sanity-check
plots for the selected dataset root.

Quick Start
-----------

Recommended local setup:

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
python -m pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

Run Commands
------------

Processing only:

```bash
python -m src.run_pipeline
```

Plots only:

```bash
python -m src.checks.plot.run_all
```

Processing and plots in one command:

```bash
python -m src.run_bump_plots
```

Notes:

- `src.run_pipeline` currently runs the save pipeline only.
- `src.run_bump_plots` is the current combined "process, then plot" entry point.
- Plot output is written under `figures/<ROOT_DIR>/...`.

Pipeline Outputs
----------------

For a dataset root such as `data/bump1`, the pipeline writes:

```text
data/bump1/calibration/PH/calibs_0.h5
data/bump1/calibration/PH/calibs_50.h5
data/bump1/calibration/PH/calibs_100.h5

data/bump1/calibration/NC/calibs_0.h5
data/bump1/calibration/NC/calibs_50.h5
data/bump1/calibration/NC/calibs_100.h5

data/bump1/pressure/F_freestreamp_SU_raw.hdf5
data/bump1/pressure/F_freestreamp_SU_production.hdf5
data/bump1/pressure/G_wallp_SU_raw.hdf5
data/bump1/pressure/G_wallp_SU_production.hdf5
```

Details:

- `calibration/PH` is produced from the PH semi-anechoic calibration runs.
- `calibration/NC` is only produced when NC calibration generation is enabled.
- `pressure/F_*` stores freestream-pressure products.
- `pressure/G_*` stores wall-pressure products.

Required Input Layout
---------------------

All paths below are relative to `PRESSUREPROCESS_ROOT_DIR` / `Config.ROOT_DIR`.

Wall-pressure runs:

```text
ROOT_DIR/raw_wallp/
  close/
    0psig.mat
    50psig.mat
    100psig.mat
  far/
    0psig.mat
    50psig.mat
    100psig.mat
```

PH calibration runs:

```text
ROOT_DIR/raw_calib/PH/
  calib_0psig_1.mat
  calib_0psig_2.mat
  calib_50psig_1.mat
  calib_50psig_2.mat
  calib_100psig_1.mat
  calib_100psig_2.mat
```

Optional NC calibration runs:

```text
ROOT_DIR/raw_calib/NC/
  0psig/
    nkd-ns_nofacilitynoise.mat
  50psig/
    nkd-ns_nofacilitynoise.mat
  100psig/
    nkd-ns_nofacilitynoise.mat
```

NC calibration files are optional. If you do not have them, leave
`RUN_NC_CALIBS = False` in `src/config_params.py` and the production stages
will fall back to an identity NC FRF.

Expected MATLAB Variables
-------------------------

Wall-pressure runs and freestream extraction expect:

```text
channelData
```

with columns ordered as:

```text
PH1, PH2, NC
```

PH calibration runs expect either:

```text
channelData_WN
```

or:

```text
channelData
```

with columns ordered as:

```text
PH1, PH2, NC, ...
```

NC calibration runs expect:

```text
channelData
```

and for the `100psig` case only:

```text
channelData_nofacitynoise
```

That `nofacitynoise` spelling is not a typo in this README; it matches the
loader's current key.

Configuration
-------------

Most settings live in `src/config_params.py`.

Common environment variables:

- `PRESSUREPROCESS_ROOT_DIR`: dataset root to read from and write into.
- `PRESSUREPROCESS_PW_DENOISER`: `auto`, `hybrid`, or `wiener`.
- `PRESSUREPROCESS_USE_TEX`: `auto`, `true`, or `false` for plot text rendering.

Important config fields in `Config`:

- `LABELS`, `PSIGS`
- `U_TAU`, `U_TAU_REL_UNC`, `U_E`
- `ANALOG_LP_FILTER`, `F_CUTS`
- `SPACINGS`
- `RUN_NC_CALIBS`
- `INCLUDE_NC_CALIB_RAW`
- `SENSITIVITIES_V_PER_PA`

Notes:

- `RUN_NC_CALIBS` defaults to `False`.
- `INCLUDE_NC_CALIB_RAW` defaults to `False`.
- `PRESSUREPROCESS_PW_DENOISER=auto` is the default. On large macOS runs, the
  code will choose the lighter hybrid wall-pressure noise canceller to reduce
  memory pressure.

Testing
-------

Run the test suite with:

```bash
pytest
```

Docker (Last Resort)
--------------------

Use Docker only if you do not want to manage a local Python environment.

Build:

```bash
docker build -t pressureprocess .
```

Run:

```bash
docker run --rm \
  --memory=8g \
  --cpus=4 \
  --user "$(id -u):$(id -g)" \
  -e PRESSUREPROCESS_ROOT_DIR=data/bump1 \
  -e PRESSUREPROCESS_USE_TEX=auto \
  -e TORCH_NUM_THREADS=1 \
  -v "$(pwd)/data:/app/data:Z" \
  -v "$(pwd)/figures:/app/figures:Z" \
  pressureprocess
```

Notes:

- `--user "$(id -u):$(id -g)"` avoids host/container ownership mismatches.
- `:Z` on bind mounts is only needed on SELinux systems such as Fedora/RHEL.
- The image installs CPU-only PyTorch and conservative thread defaults.
